cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem, and proposes a semi-supervised approach that involves deep neural networks and generative models. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves feature learning and pseudo-labeling, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The datasets used in the experiments are related to multimedia (Market-1501 and DukeMTMC-reID), so cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with surveillance camera installations, which involves security and privacy concerns, making cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) a less likely but still possible category.
